## File Changes

### Backend

#### [NEW] [planner.py](file:///d:/Mini-proj/ghmc/Browser-automation-chatbot/browser/backend/planner.py)
- `plan_actions(message, dom_snapshot, session_context)` → `PlanResponse`
- System prompt enforces JSON output with `element_id` references
- Session context tracks conversation + previous actions for multi-turn flows
- Loop detection: checks `action_history` for repetition

#### [MODIFY] [schemas.py](file:///d:/Mini-proj/ghmc/Browser-automation-chatbot/browser/backend/schemas.py)
New schemas:
- `DOMElement`: `{ id, tag, type, label, placeholder, text, name, value, visible, disabled }`
- `DOMAction`: `{ type, element_id, value, description, condition, timeout_ms }`
- `PlanRequest`: `{ message, elements: DOMElement[], page_url, session_id, action_history, loop_detected }`
- `PlanResponse`: `{ actions: DOMAction[], message, done, wait_for_user_input }`

#### [MODIFY] [main.py](file:///d:/Mini-proj/ghmc/Browser-automation-chatbot/browser/backend/main.py)
- Add `POST /plan` endpoint (calls `planner.plan_actions()`)
- Keep `POST /chat` for conversational Q&A
- Keep `POST /automate` as fallback for headless URL discovery

---

### Extension

#### [MODIFY] [content.js](file:///d:/Mini-proj/ghmc/Browser-automation-chatbot/browser/extension/content_scripts/content.js)
Major rewrite — three responsibilities:

1. **Element Abstraction Layer**: Extracts interactive elements with stable IDs, filtered and prioritized
2. **DOM Action Executor**: Receives `DOMAction[]`, resolves `element_id` → DOM element, executes with human-like events + visual highlight
3. **State Observer**: `MutationObserver` + network idle detection, waits for DOM stability between actions

Message handlers:
- `GET_DOM_SNAPSHOT` → returns `{ elements[], page_url, title }`
- `EXECUTE_ACTIONS` → executes action batch, returns `{ results[], new_snapshot }`

#### [MODIFY] [panel.js](file:///d:/Mini-proj/ghmc/Browser-automation-chatbot/browser/extension/side_panel/panel.js)
New orchestration loop:
1. Get DOM snapshot from content script
2. Send `POST /plan` with `{ message, elements, action_history }`
3. Receive `PlanResponse` → forward actions to content script
4. Content script executes + returns results
5. If `done: false` → loop (with new snapshot)
6. If `wait_for_user_input` → pause, show prompt in chat
7. Loop detection: track action_history, send flag if repeated
8. Show step-by-step progress in chat bubbles

#### [MODIFY] [panel.html](file:///d:/Mini-proj/ghmc/Browser-automation-chatbot/browser/extension/side_panel/panel.html)
- Add step progress indicator (collapsible)
- Add OTP input prompt component

---

## Communication Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant P as Side Panel
    participant CS as Content Script
    participant B as Backend /plan

    U->>P: "fill mobile 8248007169 and send OTP"
    P->>CS: GET_DOM_SNAPSHOT
    CS-->>P: {elements: [{id:el_0, label:Mobile}, {id:el_1, text:Send OTP}]}
    P->>B: POST /plan {message, elements, history:[]}
    B-->>P: {actions: [type el_0, click el_1, wait dom_change], done:false, wait:"Enter OTP"}
    P->>CS: EXECUTE_ACTIONS [type, click, wait]
    CS-->>CS: Types "8248007169" visibly, clicks Send OTP, waits for DOM
    CS-->>P: {results: [ok,ok,ok], new_snapshot}
    P->>U: "OTP sent! Please enter the OTP you received:"
    U->>P: "482916"
    P->>CS: GET_DOM_SNAPSHOT
    CS-->>P: {elements: [{id:el_5, label:OTP, otp_detected:true}]}
    P->>B: POST /plan {message:"otp 482916", elements, history}
    B-->>P: {actions: [type el_5 "482916"], done:true}
    P->>CS: EXECUTE_ACTIONS [type]
    CS-->>CS: Types OTP visibly
    P->>U: "✅ OTP entered!"
```

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated
```bash
# Backend planner unit test
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/plan -d '{"message":"fill mobile","elements":[{"id":"el_0","tag":"input","label":"Mobile"}]}'
# Expect: JSON with actions referencing el_0
```

### Manual E2E
1. Open GHMC Function Hall Booking in Chrome
2. Open side panel → "fill my mobile number 8248007169 and click send OTP"
3. **Verify**: Agent types visibly into mobile field, clicks Send OTP
4. Agent pauses → "Enter OTP"
5. User types OTP → agent fills it visibly

### Latency Target
- Single batch (3 actions): < 5 seconds total
- Multi-batch flow (6 actions): < 12 seconds total
